</SO>
<CO>
   MDEX
</CO>
<IN>
MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   HILLIARD, Ohio -- Medex Inc., which designs, makes,
assembles and markets disposable hospital products for
life-support systems, said it acquired Ivion Corp. of
Englewood, Colo., which develops and markets drug-delivery
products. Terms weren't disclosed.
   Ivion, which will retain its name, location and
management, has annual sales of $18 million. Medex has annual
sales of $44.7 million.
