<HL>
   Bank of Montreal Cuts Prime
</HL>
<DATE>
12/20/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C11
</SO>
<CO>
   T.BMO
</CO>
<IN>
BANKS (BNK)
CANADIAN ECONOMIC AND MONETARY NEWS AND ANALYSIS (CEA)
</IN>
<LP>
   TORONTO -- Bank of Montreal cut its prime lending rate to
12.75% from 13%, effective today.
   It was the bank's seventh consecutive prime-rate drop
since August. It follows the bank's reduction of one-quarter
percentage point in its prime rate last week. The prime rate
is the base for various lending charges.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Canada's other major banks are expected to lower their
prime rates today to 12.75% from 13.25%. Bank of Montreal has
recently led Canada's other banks in prime-rate reductions.
